{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883280187,"sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae45ef7001z3rWuKtqZ1KvPz","messageID":"msg_d7ae44e5e001VdndFf8Y7doP5E","sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0bf78eacc04d460f86b43905aee72dff","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: **Feature:** AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n4: **Goal:** Implement the AgentRuntimeClient in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n5: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n6: - AgentRuntimeClient provides high-level API for agent runtime interactions\n7: - Session ID is bootstrapped from Router or reused from existing session\n8: - Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n9: - Invoke method handles HTTP communication via Router with proper timeout configuration\n10: - Connection pooling is implemented via requests.Session\n11: - Error handling includes session validation and HTTP error propagation\n12: - Unit tests achieve >80% code coverage\n13: - Integration tests work with real Router service\n14: **Architecture:** Python SDK client with AgentRuntimeClient (main API) and AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (HTTP layer), following context manager pattern for resource cleanup.\n15: **Tech Stack:** Python 3.10+, requests ^2.31.0\n16: **Frontend validation:** No\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ### Task 1: Verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure\n21: \n22: **Files:**\n23: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n24: - Verify: `agentcube/__init__.py`\n25: \n26: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n27: \n28: ```python\n29: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py\n30: import pytest\n31: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n32: \n33: \n34: def test_agent_runtime_client_has_required_methods():\n35:     \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient has all required public methods.\"\"\"\n36:     required_methods = [\n37:         \"__init__\",\n38:         \"__enter__\",\n39:         \"__exit__\",\n40:         \"invoke\",\n41:         \"close\",\n42:     ]\n43: \n44:     for method_name in required_methods:\n45:         assert hasattr(AgentRuntimeClient, method_name), f\"AgentRuntimeClient missing method: {method_name}\"\n46: \n47: \n48: def test_agent_runtime_client_has_required_attributes():\n49:     \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient has all required instance attributes.\"\"\"\n50:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n51:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n52:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n53:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n54:         )\n55: \n56:     required_attributes = [\n57:         \"agent_name\",\n58:         \"namespace\",\n59:         \"timeout\",\n60:         \"connect_timeout\",\n61:         \"logger\",\n62:         \"router_url\",\n63:         \"session_id\",\n64:         \"dp_client\",\n65:         \"verbose\",\n66:     ]\n67: \n68:     for attr in required_attributes:\n69:         assert hasattr(client, attr), f\"AgentRuntimeClient missing attribute: {attr}\"\n70: \n71:     client.close()\n72: ```\n73: \n74: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n75: \n76: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py -v`\n77: Expected: PASS\n78: \n79: **Step 3: Verify AgentRuntimeClient is exported**\n80: \n81: ```python\n82: # tests/test_public_api.py\n83: import agentcube\n84: \n85: \n86: def test_agent_runtime_client_exported():\n87:     \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient is exported from agentcube package.\"\"\"\n88:     assert hasattr(agentcube, \"AgentRuntimeClient\")\n89:     assert \"AgentRuntimeClient\" in agentcube.__all__\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n93: \n94: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_public_api.py -v`\n95: Expected: PASS\n96: \n97: **Step 5: Commit**\n98: \n99: ```bash\n100: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py tests/test_public_api.py\n101: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure\"\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ### Task 2: Verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization with all parameters\n107: \n108: **Files:**\n109: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n110: - Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n111: \n112: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n113: \n114: ```python\n115: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py\n116: import os\n117: from unittest.mock import patch\n118: import pytest\n119: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n120: \n121: \n122: def test_initialization_with_all_parameters():\n123:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization with all parameters.\"\"\"\n124:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n125:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n126:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n127: \n128:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n129:             agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n130:             namespace=\"production\",\n131:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n132:             verbose=True,\n133:             session_id=\"existing-session\",\n134:             timeout=180,\n135:             connect_timeout=10.0,\n136:         )\n137: \n138:         assert client.agent_name == \"my-agent\"\n139:         assert client.namespace == \"production\"\n140:         assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n141:         assert client.verbose is True\n142:         assert client.session_id == \"existing-session\"\n143:         assert client.timeout == 180\n144:         assert client.connect_timeout == 10.0\n145: \n146:         # Verify bootstrap_session_id was NOT called when session_id is provided\n147:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_not_called()\n148: \n149:         client.close()\n150: \n151: \n152: def test_initialization_defaults():\n153:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization with default values.\"\"\"\n154:     with patch.dict(os.environ, {\"ROUTER_URL\": \"http://router:8080\"}):\n155:         with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n156:             mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n157:             mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n158: \n159:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n160: \n161:             assert client.agent_name == \"my-agent\"\n162:             assert client.namespace == \"default\"\n163:             assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n164:             assert client.verbose is False\n165:             assert client.timeout == 120\n166:             assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n167: \n168:             # Verify bootstrap_session_id was called when session_id is NOT provided\n169:             mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_called_once()\n170: \n171:             client.close()\n172: \n173: \n174: def test_initialization_without_router_url_and_env():\n175:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization without router_url or env var.\"\"\"\n176:     with patch.dict(os.environ, {}, clear=True):\n177:         with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n178:             mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n179:             mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n180: \n181:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n182: \n183:             assert client.router_url == \"\"\n184:             assert client.logger.warning.called\n185: \n186:             client.close()\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n190: \n191: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py -v`\n192: Expected: PASS\n193: \n194: **Step 3: Commit**\n195: \n196: ```bash\n197: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py\n198: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization\"\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ### Task 3: Verify AgentRuntimeClient context manager support\n204: \n205: **Files:**\n206: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n207: - Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n208: \n209: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py\n213: import pytest\n214: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n215: \n216: \n217: def test_context_manager_enter_returns_self():\n218:     \"\"\"Test __enter__ returns self.\"\"\"\n219:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n220:         with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\") as client:\n221:             assert isinstance(client, AgentRuntimeClient)\n222: \n223: \n224: def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close():\n225:     \"\"\"Test __exit__ calls close method.\"\"\"\n226:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n227:         with pytest.mock.patch.object(AgentRuntimeClient, \"close\") as mock_close:\n228:             with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\"):\n229:                 pass\n230: \n231:             mock_close.assert_called_once()\n232: \n233: \n234: def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close_on_exception():\n235:     \"\"\"Test __exit__ calls close method even when exception occurs.\"\"\"\n236:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n237:         with pytest.mock.patch.object(AgentRuntimeClient, \"close\") as mock_close:\n238:             with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n239:                 with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\"):\n240:                     raise ValueError(\"Test error\")\n241: \n242:             mock_close.assert_called_once()\n243: \n244: \n245: def test_close_is_idempotent():\n246:     \"\"\"Test close can be called multiple times without error.\"\"\"\n247:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n248:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n249: \n250:         # First close\n251:         client.close()\n252: \n253:         # Second close should not raise\n254:         client.close()\n255: ```\n256: \n257: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n258: \n259: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py -v`\n260: Expected: PASS\n261: \n262: **Step 3: Commit**\n263: \n264: ```bash\n265: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py\n266: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient context manager support\"\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### Task 4: Verify AgentRuntimeClient invoke method\n272: \n273: **Files:**\n274: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n275: - Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n276: \n277: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n278: \n279: ```python\n280: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py\n281: import pytest\n282: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n283: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n284: \n285: \n286: def test_invoke_success():\n287:     \"\"\"Test invoke method with successful response.\"\"\"\n288:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n289:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n290:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n291: \n292:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n293:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test\"}\n294:         mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n295: \n296:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n297: \n298:         payload = {\"query\": \"test query\"}\n299:         result = client.invoke(payload)\n300: \n301:         assert result == {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test\"}\n302:         mock_dp_instance.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n303:             \"test-session-id\", payload, timeout=None\n304:         )\n305: \n306:         client.close()\n307: \n308: \n309: def test_invoke_with_custom_timeout():\n310:     \"\"\"Test invoke method with custom timeout.\"\"\"\n311:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n312:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n313:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n314: \n315:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n316:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n317:         mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n318: \n319:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n320: \n321:         payload = {\"query\": \"test query\"}\n322:         result = client.invoke(payload, timeout=60.0)\n323: \n324:         assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n325:         mock_dp_instance.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n326:             \"test-session-id\", payload, timeout=60.0\n327:         )\n328: \n329:         client.close()\n330: \n331: \n332: def test_invoke_without_session_id_raises_error():\n333:     \"\"\"Test invoke raises ValueError when session_id is not initialized.\"\"\"\n334:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n335:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n336:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = None\n337: \n338:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n339:         client.session_id = None\n340: \n341:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"):\n342:             client.invoke({\"query\": \"test\"})\n343: \n344:         client.close()\n345: \n346: \n347: def test_invoke_with_various_payloads():\n348:     \"\"\"Test invoke with various payload types.\"\"\"\n349:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n350:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n351:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n352: \n353:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n354:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n355:         mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n356: \n357:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n358: \n359:         # Test with dict\n360:         result1 = client.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})\n361:         assert result1 == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n362: \n363:         # Test with nested dict\n364:         result2 = client.invoke({\"nested\": {\"key\": \"value\"}})\n365:         assert result2 == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n366: \n367:         # Test with array\n368:         result3 = client.invoke({\"items\": [1, 2, 3]})\n369:         assert result3 == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n370: \n371:         client.close()\n372: ```\n373: \n374: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n375: \n376: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py -v`\n377: Expected: PASS\n378: \n379: **Step 3: Commit**\n380: \n381: ```bash\n382: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py\n383: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient invoke method\"\n384: ```\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ### Task 5: Verify AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implementation\n389: \n390: **Files:**\n391: - Verify: `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n392: - Create: `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n393: \n394: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n395: \n396: ```python\n397: # tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n398: import pytest\n399: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n400: from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n401: \n402: \n403: def test_data_plane_client_initialization():\n404:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient initialization.\"\"\"\n405:     client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n406:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n407:         namespace=\"production\",\n408:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n409:         timeout=180,\n410:         connect_timeout=10.0,\n411:         pool_connections=20,\n412:         pool_maxsize=20,\n413:     )\n414: \n415:     assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n416:     assert client.namespace == \"production\"\n417:     assert client.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n418:     assert client.timeout == 180\n419:     assert client.connect_timeout == 10.0\n420:     assert client.base_url == \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/production/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n421: \n422:     client.close()\n423: \n424: \n425: def test_bootstrap_session_id_success():\n426:     \"\"\"Test bootstrap_session_id returns session ID from header.\"\"\"\n427:     with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n428:         mock_session = MagicMock()\n429:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n430:         mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-123\"}\n431:         mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n432:         mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n433: \n434:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n435:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n436:             namespace=\"default\",\n437:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n438:         )\n439: \n440:         session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n441: \n442:         assert session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n443:         mock_session.get.assert_called_once_with(\n444:             client.base_url,\n445:             timeout=(5.0, 120)\n446:         )\n447: \n448:         client.close()\n449: \n450: \n451: def test_bootstrap_session_id_missing_header_raises_error():\n452:     \"\"\"Test bootstrap_session_id raises ValueError when header is missing.\"\"\"\n453:     with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n454:         mock_session = MagicMock()\n455:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n456:         mock_response.headers = {}\n457:         mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n458:         mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n459: \n460:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n461:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n462:             namespace=\"default\",\n463:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n464:         )\n465: \n466:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header\"):\n467:             client.bootstrap_session_id()\n468: \n469:         client.close()\n470: \n471: \n472: def test_invoke_success():\n473:     \"\"\"Test invoke method with successful response.\"\"\"\n474:     with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n475:         mock_session = MagicMock()\n476:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n477:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n478:         mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n479:         mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n480: \n481:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n482:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n483:             namespace=\"default\",\n484:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n485:         )\n486: \n487:         payload = {\"query\": \"test\"}\n488:         response = client.invoke(\"session-123\", payload)\n489: \n490:         assert response.json() == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n491:         mock_session.post.assert_called_once_with(\n492:             client.base_url,\n493:             json=payload,\n494:             headers={\n495:                 \"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\",\n496:                 \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n497:             },\n498:             timeout=(5.0, 120)\n499:         )\n500: \n501:         client.close()\n502: \n503: \n504: def test_invoke_with_custom_timeout():\n505:     \"\"\"Test invoke method with custom timeout.\"\"\"\n506:     with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n507:         mock_session = MagicMock()\n508:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n509:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n510:         mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n511:         mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n512: \n513:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n514:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n515:             namespace=\"default\",\n516:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n517:         )\n518: \n519:         payload = {\"query\": \"test\"}\n520:         response = client.invoke(\"session-123\", payload, timeout=60.0)\n521: \n522:         assert response.json() == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n523:         mock_session.post.assert_called_once_with(\n524:             client.base_url,\n525:             json=payload,\n526:             headers={\n527:                 \"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\",\n528:                 \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n529:             },\n530:             timeout=(5.0, 60.0)  # Custom read timeout\n531:         )\n532: \n533:         client.close()\n534: \n535: \n536: def test_session_header_constant():\n537:     \"\"\"Test SESSION_HEADER constant.\"\"\"\n538:     assert AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER == \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n5