{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883482330,"sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae70ff7001WrZdK2YRhK39fE","messageID":"msg_d7ae545270016POkQv3YjmY65B","sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-962b5ede45134516b24ad2f81b583c7c","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建\n\n## Overview\n\nThis implementation provides a multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project, using three independent build stages to create optimized production images.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Multi-Stage Architecture**: Three-stage build (Builder → Verifier → Runtime)\n- **Optimized Images**: Minimal runtime image size (~150-250 MB)\n- **Security**: Non-privileged user execution, minimal attack surface\n- **Flexibility**: Support for multiple image variants (production, development, test)\n- **Multi-Architecture**: Support for Linux AMD64 and ARM64\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Build Production Image\n\n```bash\n./build.sh runtime\n```\n\nThis builds the production runtime image with tag `agentcube:latest`.\n\n### Build All Targets\n\n```bash\n./build.sh all\n```\n\nThis builds all three targets:\n- `agentcube:dev` - Builder image for development\n- `agentcube:test` - Verifier image with tests\n- `agentcube:latest` - Production runtime image\n\n### Multi-Architecture Build\n\n```bash\n./build-multiarch.sh --push --platforms linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n```\n\n## Build Targets\n\n### Stage 1: Builder\n\nThe builder stage compiles all binaries and installs dependencies:\n\n- **Base Image**: `golang:1.21-alpine`\n- **Output**: Development image tagged `agentcube:dev`\n- **Size**: ~800-1200 MB\n\n```bash\ndocker build --target builder -t agentcube:dev .\n```\n\n### Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)\n\nThe verifier stage runs tests on build artifacts:\n\n- **Base Image**: Inherits from builder\n- **Output**: Test image tagged `agentcube:test`\n- **Size**: ~850-1250 MB\n\n```bash\ndocker build --target verifier -t agentcube:test .\n```\n\n### Stage 3: Runtime\n\nThe runtime stage contains only production artifacts:\n\n- **Base Image**: `alpine:3.19`\n- **Output**: Production image tagged `agentcube:latest`\n- **Size**: ~150-250 MB\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t agentcube:latest .\n```\n\n## Build Arguments\n\n| Argument | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.21` | Go compiler version |\n| `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | Alpine Linux version |\n| `BUILD_VERSION` | `dev` | Application version |\n| `BUILD_TIME` | (auto) | Build timestamp |\n| `GIT_COMMIT` | (auto) | Git commit hash |\n\n### Example: Custom Build Arguments\n\n```bash\ndocker build \\\n  --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_TIME=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \\\n  --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) \\\n  -t agentcube:v1.0.0 \\\n  .\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_ENV` | `production` | Runtime environment |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | Logging level |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT` | `json` | Log format (json/text) |\n| `AGENTCUBE_PORT` | `8080` | Service port |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable metrics endpoint |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT` | `9090` | Metrics port |\n\n## Validation\n\n### Build Validation\n\nRun comprehensive build validation:\n\n```bash\n./validate-build.sh\n```\n\nThis validates:\n- Dockerfile syntax\n- Base image availability\n- All targets build successfully\n- Image sizes and layers\n- Non-root user configuration\n- Binary execution\n- Image metadata\n\n### Runtime Validation\n\nRun runtime container validation:\n\n```bash\n./validate-runtime.sh\n```\n\nThis validates:\n- Container startup\n- Non-root user execution\n- File permissions and ownership\n- Python installation\n- Environment variables\n- Resource limits\n- Network connectivity\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Running the Container\n\n```bash\n# Basic run\ndocker run -d -p 8080:8080 agentcube:latest\n\n# With custom environment variables\ndocker run -d \\\n  -p 8080:8080 \\\n  -e AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL=debug \\\n  -e AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT=text \\\n  agentcube:latest\n\n# With resource limits\ndocker run -d \\\n  -p 8080:8080 \\\n  --memory=\"512m\" \\\n  --cpus=\"1.0\" \\\n  agentcube:latest\n\n# With volume mount\ndocker run -d \\\n  -p 8080:8080 \\\n  -v /data/agentcube:/app/data \\\n  agentcube:latest\n```\n\n### Development Workflow\n\n```bash\n# 1. Build development image\n./build.sh builder -t agentcube:dev\n\n# 2. Run development container\ndocker run -it --rm agentcube:dev /bin/sh\n\n# 3. Make changes to code\n\n# 4. Rebuild development image\n./build.sh builder -t agentcube:dev\n```\n\n### Multi-Architecture Build and Push\n\n```bash\n# Build and push to registry\nREGISTRY=ghcr.io/your-org \\\nBUILD_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n./build-multiarch.sh --push -t v1.0.0\n\n# Build and load locally (single platform)\n./build-multiarch.sh --local --platforms linux/amd64\n```\n\n## Security Features\n\n- **Non-privileged user**: Runs as `agentcube` (UID 1000)\n- **Minimal base**: Uses Alpine Linux (~5MB base)\n- **No build tools**: Compilers and build tools excluded from runtime\n- **Minimal dependencies**: Only runtime dependencies included\n- **Health checks**: Built-in health check endpoint\n- **Read-only root**: Optionally use read-only root filesystem\n\n## Performance Optimizations\n\n- **Layer caching**: Optimized Dockerfile layer ordering for cache hits\n- **Dependency caching**: Go dependencies downloaded before source code\n- **Multi-stage**: Build tools discarded in final image\n- **Binary stripping**: Compiled with `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"` for smaller binaries\n- **No-cache pip**: Python packages installed without cache\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Build Failures\n\n**Issue**: Go compilation errors\n```bash\n# Check Go version compatibility\ndocker run --rm golang:1.21-alpine go version\n\n# Verify dependencies\ndocker run --rm -v $(pwd):/app -w /app golang:1.21-alpine go mod verify\n```\n\n**Issue**: Python dependency errors\n```bash\n# Check requirements.txt syntax\ndocker run --rm python:3.11-alpine pip check\n\n# Test dependencies installation\ndocker run --rm -v $(pwd):/app -w /app python:3.11-alpine pip install -r requirements.txt --dry-run\n```\n\n### Runtime Failures\n\n**Issue**: Container won't start\n```bash\n# Check container logs\ndocker logs <container-id>\n\n# Inspect container status\ndocker inspect <container-id>\n\n# Test binary execution\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest /app/agentd version\n```\n\n**Issue**: Permission errors\n```bash\n# Check user\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest whoami\n\n# Check file permissions\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest ls -la /app/agentd\n\n# Check file ownership\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest stat -c '%U:%G' /app/agentd\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\n.\n├── Dockerfile              # Multi-stage Dockerfile\n├── .dockerignore           # Files excluded from build context\n├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies\n├── build.sh                # Single-arch build script\n├── build-multiarch.sh      # Multi-arch build script\n├── validate-build.sh       # Build validation script\n├── validate-runtime.sh     # Runtime validation script\n└── README.md              # This file\n```\n\n## CI/CD Integration\n\n### GitHub Actions Example\n\n```yaml\nname: Build and Push\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    tags: ['v*']\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      \n      - name: Set up Docker Buildx\n        uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v2\n      \n      - name: Login to GHCR\n        uses: docker/login-action@v2\n        with:\n          registry: ghcr.io\n          username: ${{ github.actor }}\n          password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n      \n      - name: Build and push\n        run: |\n          REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }} \\\n          BUILD_VERSION=${{ github.ref_name }} \\\n          ./build-multiarch.sh --push\n```\n\n## Metrics and Monitoring\n\nThe image exposes the following ports:\n\n- **8080**: Main application port\n- **9090**: Metrics endpoint (Prometheus format)\n\nAccess metrics:\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:9090/metrics\n```\n\nHealth check:\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:8080/healthz\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\nWhen modifying the Dockerfile:\n\n1. Test all build targets: `./build.sh all`\n2. Run build validation: `./validate-build.sh`\n3. Run runtime validation: `./validate-runtime.sh`\n4. Verify image size is acceptable (< 250 MB)\n5. Test multi-architecture build: `./build-multiarch.sh --local`\n\n## License\n\nSee [LICENSE](../../LICENSE) for details.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/README.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/README.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775883482299,"end":1775883482328}}}}
