{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883558448,"sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae85196001s5FyQVhvvqOBlg","messageID":"msg_d7ae7f962001SF34X6iAEJ18eg","sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-94c3b4be2ebb45bfacbf4c7b003f6faa","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-032: Dockerfile Multi-Stage Build - Implementation Summary\n\n## Implementation Status\n\n✅ **COMPLETE** - All components implemented and tested\n\n## Overview\n\nThis implementation provides a comprehensive multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project, featuring three independent build stages (Builder, Verifier, Runtime) to create optimized production images.\n\n## Files Created\n\n### Core Docker Files\n- **Dockerfile** - Multi-stage Dockerfile with 3 build stages\n- **.dockerignore** - Build context exclusions\n- **requirements.txt** - Python dependencies for picod\n\n### Build Scripts\n- **build.sh** - Single-architecture build script with multiple target support\n- **build-multiarch.sh** - Multi-architecture build script for linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n\n### Validation Scripts\n- **validate-build.sh** - Comprehensive build validation (12 tests)\n- **validate-runtime.sh** - Runtime container validation (17 tests)\n- **test.sh** - Automated test suite (50+ tests)\n\n### Documentation\n- **README.md** - Comprehensive user documentation\n- **IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md** - This file\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Build Stages\n\n#### Stage 1: Builder\n- **Base**: `golang:1.21-alpine`\n- **Purpose**: Compile binaries and install dependencies\n- **Output**: Development image (~800-1200 MB)\n- **Artifacts**:\n  - Compiled `agentd` binary\n  - Python site-packages\n  - PicoD source code\n\n#### Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)\n- **Base**: Inherits from builder\n- **Purpose**: Run tests and quality checks\n- **Output**: Test image (~850-1250 MB)\n- **Tests**:\n  - Go unit tests with coverage\n  - Python unit tests\n  - Test report generation\n\n#### Stage 3: Runtime\n- **Base**: `alpine:3.19`\n- **Purpose**: Production-ready minimal image\n- **Output**: Production image (~150-250 MB)\n- **Features**:\n  - Non-privileged user (agentcube:1000)\n  - Health checks\n  - Metrics endpoint\n  - Security hardening\n\n## Build Arguments\n\n| Argument | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.21` | Go compiler version |\n| `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | Alpine Linux version |\n| `BUILD_VERSION` | `dev` | Application version |\n| `BUILD_TIME` | (auto) | Build timestamp |\n| `GIT_COMMIT` | (auto) | Git commit hash |\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_ENV` | `production` | Runtime environment |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | Logging level |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT` | `json` | Log format |\n| `AGENTCUBE_PORT` | `8080` | Service port |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable metrics |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT` | `9090` | Metrics port |\n\n## Security Features\n\n1. **Non-privileged execution**: Runs as `agentcube` (UID 1000)\n2. **Minimal base image**: Alpine Linux (~5MB)\n3. **No build tools**: Compilers excluded from runtime\n4. **Minimal dependencies**: Only runtime essentials\n5. **Health checks**: Built-in health endpoint\n6. **Secure labels**: OCI-compliant image labels\n\n## Performance Optimizations\n\n1. **Layer caching**: Optimized instruction ordering\n2. **Dependency caching**: Go deps before source code\n3. **Multi-stage**: Build tools discarded\n4. **Binary stripping**: `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`\n5. **No-cache pip**: Smaller Python layer\n\n## Testing\n\n### Build Validation Tests (12)\n1. Dockerfile syntax check\n2. Base image availability\n3. Builder image build\n4. Verifier image build\n5. Runtime image build\n6. Image size verification\n7. Layer count check\n8. Non-root user verification\n9. Binary execution test\n10. Image metadata check\n11. Exposed ports verification\n12. Healthcheck configuration\n\n### Runtime Validation Tests (17)\n1. Container startup\n2. Container logs\n3. Non-root user execution\n4. Working directory\n5. File permissions\n6. File ownership\n7. Binary availability\n8. Python installation\n9. Python packages\n10. PicoD directory\n11. Environment variables\n12. Resource limits\n13. Volume mounting\n14. Network connectivity\n15. Image size\n16. Layer count\n17. Base image verification\n\n### Automated Test Suite (50+)\n- File structure tests\n- Dockerfile syntax tests\n- .dockerignore tests\n- requirements.txt tests\n- Build script tests\n- Validation script tests\n- README tests\n- Docker build tests\n- Image configuration tests\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Basic Build\n```bash\n./build.sh runtime\n```\n\n### Build All Targets\n```bash\n./build.sh all\n```\n\n### Multi-Architecture Build\n```bash\n./build-multiarch.sh --push --platforms linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n```\n\n### Validate Build\n```bash\n./validate-build.sh\n```\n\n### Validate Runtime\n```bash\n./validate-runtime.sh\n```\n\n### Run Tests\n```bash\n./test.sh\n```\n\n## CI/CD Integration\n\nThe implementation includes CI/CD-ready scripts that can be integrated with:\n- GitHub Actions\n- GitLab CI/CD\n- Jenkins\n- Other CI/CD platforms\n\nSee README.md for GitHub Actions example.\n\n## Metrics and Monitoring\n\n### Exposed Ports\n- **8080**: Main application port\n- **9090**: Metrics endpoint (Prometheus format)\n\n### Endpoints\n- `/healthz`: Health check endpoint\n- `/metrics`: Prometheus metrics endpoint\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\nSee README.md for comprehensive troubleshooting guide covering:\n- Build failures\n- Runtime failures\n- Permission errors\n- Network issues\n- Resource constraints\n\n## Performance Metrics\n\n### Target Metrics\n- **Build Time** (cached): < 5 minutes\n- **Image Size**: < 250 MB\n- **Layer Count**: < 15\n- **Cache Hit Rate**: > 70%\n- **Startup Time**: < 10 seconds\n- **Memory Usage**: < 200 MB\n\n## Compliance\n\n### Security Compliance\n- ✅ Non-root user execution\n- ✅ Minimal base image\n- ✅ No build tools in runtime\n- ✅ Secure file permissions\n- ✅ Health checks enabled\n\n### Best Practices\n- ✅ Dockerfile best practices (Hadolint compliant)\n- ✅ Multi-stage builds\n- ✅ Layer caching optimization\n- ✅ .dockerignore for minimal context\n- ✅ OCI-compliant labels\n\n## Documentation\n\n### User Documentation\n- README.md: Comprehensive user guide\n- Quick start examples\n- Usage examples\n- Troubleshooting guide\n- CI/CD integration examples\n\n### Developer Documentation\n- Build script comments\n- Validation script comments\n- Inline Dockerfile comments\n- Test script documentation\n\n## Next Steps\n\n### Recommended Enhancements\n1. Add security scanning (Trivy/Docker Scout)\n2. Implement SBOM generation\n3. Add image signing (cosign/notary)\n4. Implement image provenance\n5. Add vulnerability reporting\n6. Implement image versioning strategy\n\n### Optional Features\n1. Read-only root filesystem\n2. Seccomp profiles\n3. AppArmor profiles\n4. Custom CA certificates\n5. Runtime security policies\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThis implementation provides a production-ready, secure, and optimized multi-stage Dockerfile build system for the AgentCube project. All components have been implemented, tested, and documented according to the design specifications.\n\nThe implementation includes:\n- ✅ 3-stage multi-stage Dockerfile\n- ✅ Build and validation scripts\n- ✅ Comprehensive test suite\n- ✅ Complete documentation\n- ✅ CI/CD integration ready\n- ✅ Security best practices\n- ✅ Performance optimizations\n\n## Contact\n\nFor questions or issues related to this implementation, please refer to the main project documentation or open an issue in the project repository.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775883558438,"end":1775883558447}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883558453,"sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae89e13001LvjHH4IJfODvJ0","messageID":"msg_d7ae7f962001SF34X6iAEJ18eg","sessionID":"ses_2851bd0c0ffe9IJwZuO7AIFQRD","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-26ee2ca175f24e509389d2efa36768ed","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Makefile for AR-032 Dockerfile Multi-Stage Build\n\n.PHONY: help build build-all build-multiarch validate validate-build validate-runtime test clean\n\n# Default target\n.DEFAULT_GOAL := help\n\n# Variables\nGO_VERSION ?= 1.21\nBUILD_VERSION ?= dev\nBUILD_TIME ?= $(shell date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\nGIT_COMMIT ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo 'unknown')\nIMAGE_NAME ?= agentcube\nTAG ?= latest\nREGISTRY ?=\nPLATFORMS ?= linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n\n# Colors\nBLUE := \\033[0;34m\nGREEN := \\033[0;32m\nYELLOW := \\033[1;33m\nNC := \\033[0m\n\nhelp: ## Show this help message\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)AgentCube Docker Multi-Stage Build$(NC)\"\n\t@echo \"\"\n\t@echo \"$(GREEN)Usage:$(NC)\"\n\t@echo \"  make [target]\"\n\t@echo \"\"\n\t@echo \"$(GREEN)Targets:$(NC)\"\n\t@awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*?## \"} /^[a-zA-Z_-]+:.*?## / {printf \"  $(YELLOW)%-15s$(NC) %s\\n\", $$1, $$2}' $(MAKEFILE_LIST)\n\t@echo \"\"\n\t@echo \"$(GREEN)Variables:$(NC)\"\n\t@echo \"  GO_VERSION      Go version (default: $(GO_VERSION))\"\n\t@echo \"  BUILD_VERSION   Build version (default: $(BUILD_VERSION))\"\n\t@echo \"  BUILD_TIME      Build timestamp (default: $(BUILD_TIME))\"\n\t@echo \"  GIT_COMMIT      Git commit (default: $(GIT_COMMIT))\"\n\t@echo \"  IMAGE_NAME      Image name (default: $(IMAGE_NAME))\"\n\t@echo \"  TAG             Image tag (default: $(TAG))\"\n\t@echo \"  REGISTRY        Container registry (default: $(REGISTRY))\"\n\t@echo \"  PLATFORMS       Platforms for multi-arch (default: $(PLATFORMS))\"\n\nbuild: ## Build production runtime image\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Building production image...$(NC)\"\n\t@./build.sh runtime -t $(TAG)\n\nbuild-builder: ## Build builder (development) image\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Building builder image...$(NC)\"\n\t@./build.sh builder -t $(TAG)\n\nbuild-verifier: ## Build verifier (test) image\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Building verifier image...$(NC)\"\n\t@./build.sh verifier -t $(TAG)\n\nbuild-all: ## Build all targets (builder, verifier, runtime)\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Building all targets...$(NC)\"\n\t@./build.sh all\n\nbuild-multiarch: ## Build multi-architecture images\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Building multi-architecture images...$(NC)\"\n\t@./build-multiarch.sh --platforms $(PLATFORMS)\n\nbuild-multiarch-push: ## Build and push multi-architecture images\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Building and pushing multi-architecture images...$(NC)\"\n\t@REGISTRY=$(REGISTRY) BUILD_VERSION=$(BUILD_VERSION) ./build-multiarch.sh --push -t $(TAG)\n\nvalidate: validate-build validate-runtime ## Run all validations\n\nvalidate-build: ## Validate build process\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Validating build process...$(NC)\"\n\t@./validate-build.sh\n\nvalidate-runtime: ## Validate runtime container\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Validating runtime container...$(NC)\"\n\t@./validate-runtime.sh\n\ntest: ## Run test suite\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Running test suite...$(NC)\"\n\t@./test.sh\n\nclean: ## Clean up Docker images and containers\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Cleaning up...$(NC)\"\n\t@docker rmi $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n\t@docker rmi $(IMAGE_NAME):dev 2>/dev/null || true\n\t@docker rmi $(IMAGE_NAME):test 2>/dev/null || true\n\t@docker system prune -f\n\nclean-build: ## Clean up build cache\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Cleaning build cache...$(NC)\"\n\t@docker builder prune -f\n\nclean-all: clean clean-build ## Clean up everything\n\ninspect: ## Inspect built image\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Inspecting image: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@docker inspect $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)\n\nhistory: ## Show image history\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Image history: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@docker history $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)\n\nsize: ## Show image size\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Image size: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@docker images $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG) --format \"table {{.Repository}}\\t{{.Tag}}\\t{{.Size}}\"\n\nrun: ## Run the container\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Running container: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -p 9090:9090 --name agentcube $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)\n\nlogs: ## Show container logs\n\t@docker logs agentcube\n\nstop: ## Stop running container\n\t@docker stop agentcube\n\nrm: ## Remove container\n\t@docker rm agentcube\n\nbash: ## Open shell in running container\n\t@docker exec -it agentcube /bin/sh\n\npush: ## Push image to registry\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Pushing image: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@if [ -z \"$(REGISTRY)\" ]; then \\\n\t\techo \"$(YELLOW)Warning: REGISTRY not set, pushing to Docker Hub$(NC)\"; \\\n\t\tdocker push $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG); \\\n\telse \\\n\t\tdocker tag $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG) $(REGISTRY)/$(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG); \\\n\t\tdocker push $(REGISTRY)/$(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG); \\\n\tfi\n\npull: ## Pull image from registry\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Pulling image: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@if [ -z \"$(REGISTRY)\" ]; then \\\n\t\tdocker pull $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG); \\\n\telse \\\n\t\tdocker pull $(REGISTRY)/$(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG); \\\n\t\tdocker tag $(REGISTRY)/$(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG) $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG); \\\n\tfi\n\ntag: ## Tag image with additional tag\n\t@if [ -z \"$(NEW_TAG)\" ]; then \\\n\t\techo \"$(YELLOW)Usage: make tag NEW_TAG=<tag>$(NC)\"; \\\n\t\texit 1; \\\n\tfi\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Tagging image: $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG) -> $(IMAGE_NAME):$(NEW_TAG)$(NC)\"\n\t@docker tag $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG) $(IMAGE_NAME):$(NEW_TAG)\n\nscan: ## Scan image for vulnerabilities (requires Trivy)\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Scanning image for vulnerabilities...$(NC)\"\n\t@docker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n\t\taquasec/trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL $(IMAGE_NAME):$(TAG)\n\nlint: ## Lint Dockerfile (requires Hadolint)\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Linting Dockerfile...$(NC)\"\n\t@docker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint < Dockerfile\n\ninfo: ## Show build information\n\t@echo \"$(BLUE)Build Information:$(NC)\"\n\t@echo \"  Go Version:    $(GO_VERSION)\"\n\t@echo \"  Build Version: $(BUILD_VERSION)\"\n\t@echo \"  Build Time:    $(BUILD_TIME)\"\n\t@echo \"  Git Commit:    $(GIT_COMMIT)\"\n\t@echo \"  Image Name:    $(IMAGE_NAME)\"\n\t@echo \"  Tag:           $(TAG)\"\n\t@echo \"  Registry:      $(REGISTRY)\"\n\t@echo \"  Platforms:     $(PLATFORMS)\"","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/Makefile"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/test.sh":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/Makefile","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/Makefile","time":{"start":1775883558444,"end":1775883558451}}}}
